# Kurag, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Kurag (; Aghul: Курягъ) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Kuragsky Selsoviet, Agulsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 421 as of 2010.
Geography
Kurag is located on the Koshanapu River, 18&nbsp;km northeast of Tpig (the district's administrative centre) by road. Khudig is the nearest rural locality.
